24 SECTION 1. Arkansas Code Title 5, Chapter 18, Subchapter 1, is amended
25 to add an additional section to read as follows:
26 5-18-108. Unlawful use of a communication device during the commission
27 of a human trafficking offense.
28 (a)(1) As used in this section, “communication device” means any
29 public or private instrumentality used or useful in the transmission of a
30 writing, sign, signal, picture, or sound of any kind.
31 (2) “Communication device” includes without limitation mail,
32 telephone, wire, radio, and any other means of communication.
33 (b) A person commits the offense of unlawful use of a communication
34 device during the commission of a human trafficking offense if he or she
35 knowingly uses any communication device in committing or in causing or
36 facilitating the commission of any act constituting a:
